## Component rules

- **Props:** `{ section: <SectionType>; lang: Locale }` — always exactly this shape.
- **Default:** React Server Component unless interactivity (carousel, accordion, GSAP client animation) is required.
- **Allowed shared UI:** `<Container>`, `<Button>`, `<Media>`, `<RichText>`, `<Accordion>`, `<Card>`, `<Heading>`, `<ArrowInCircle>`.
- **CSS:** `--palette-*` / `--color-*` variables only. No hardcoded hex values.
- **Animation:** Add `className={REVEAL_ITEM}` (from `src/lib/animation-classes.ts`) to elements that stagger on scroll. Import the constant; do not use the bare string `"reveal-item"` in new files.
- **Images:** Use `<Media image={section.image} ... />` — never raw `<img>`.
- **Links:** Use `resolveLink(url, lang)` from `src/lib/utils/links.ts` for `WpAcfLink` → `{ href, label, target }`.
- **Rich text / WYSIWYG:** Use `<RichText html={...} />` — never `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` directly.

### File convention

New sections: create `src/components/sections/<kebab-layout-name>/index.tsx`.

Older sections use a named file (e.g. `BenefitsGridSection.tsx`) — do not refactor those; new sections always use `index.tsx`.

**Exception — `case-study-body/`:** four section types share one folder (`CaseStudyChapterSection`, `CaseStudyProductShotSection`, `CaseStudyClientReviewSection`, `CaseStudyConversionCtaSection`). Do not replicate this pattern for new sections.

### Registry import convention

Sections registered as **static imports** (top of `section-registry.ts`): older / typically above-the-fold sections (hero, cards, cta, etc.).
Sections registered as **`next/dynamic` lazy** (`ssr: true`): most newer sections. New sections should follow the dynamic pattern.

